Poultry Association of Zambia Executive Manager, Dominic Chanda says that some producers scaled down on production due to uncertainties surrounding the policy direction aimed at curbing the outbreak of the coronavirus. Chanda says policy direction uncertainties and the closure of certain sectors specifically the tourism sector which resulted in the closure of hotels, lodges and restriction on the number of gatherings of entertainment in nature resulted in a number of small-scale, medium, commercial and large-scale poultry farmers to scale down their broiler bird placement. --ZambiaDailyMail--